org.ensor.data.atom

Class ImmutableDict

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ensor.data.atom.Atom
      • org.ensor.data.atom.ImmutableDict
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Map.Entry<String,Atom>>, IDictionaryVisitable

    public final class ImmutableDict
extends Atom
implements Iterable<Map.Entry<String,Atom>>
    This class is an immutable version of the DictionaryAtom container. It is threadsafe by virtue of the fact that it cannot change and therefore threads cannot have different views of this object. It also ensures that different event and thread handlers have the same view of the data contained within this container.
    Author:
    Jon

      • newAtom

        public static ImmutableDict newAtom(Map.Entry<String,Atom>[] entries)
        This method returns an immutable dictionary consisting of the given entries. If any of the entries given are not immutable, they are converted into their immutable counterparts before adding them to the collection.
        Parameters:
        entries - An array of entries to add to the immutable collection.
        Returns:
        An immutable dictionary consisting of the entries given converted (if necessary) into immutable objects first.

      • newAtom

        public static ImmutableDict newAtom(ImmutableDict aDict)
        This method constructs a new immutable dictionary object from the given immutable dictionary. This method actually just returns the dictionary object given because there is really no point in creating a new copy of an already immutable object.
        Parameters:
        aDict - The immutable object to copy.
        Returns:
        A copy (really a reference to the same object) of the given immutable dictionary.

      • newAtom

        public static ImmutableDict newAtom(DictionaryAtom aDict)
        This method creates a copy of the given dictionary which is immutable. The given dictionary is mutable, thus a copy of the elements of the dictionary as well as a deep copy of all of the elements below it must be made in order to ensure that this dictionary is really immutable.
        Parameters:
        aDict - A mutable dictionary to create a copy of.
        Returns:
        An immutable copy of the given dictionary.
